Hi, this encoding, while not bad, looks a bit "blocky" to me, I've certainly seen better.  However as it's off a screener maybe the original wasn't perfect.  Should please your kids but if you are a person who tends to notice the digitisation of lower bitrate encoding you might see it on this.  Credit to the original seeder though for making the effort to rip and subtitle and seed though, don't see this as flaming or anything.  Maxinedaz - you can usually burn images which are around the 4GB size with DVDdecrypter (free).  Try the guides on www.doom9.org if you are new to all this.  Respect to the community.
